div.div:
Each platform has its own unique ways of connecting to
and reading data from a Bluetooth Device.
However the core logic for converting the binary messages
from each smartcube into a useable format should be shareable
across all platforms and devices.
Thus the benefit of creating a common interface for a
BluetoothDevice that a BluetoothPuzzle can use to add listeners
and pull data, regardless of the underlying platform.
An alternative implementation would only offer the transformation
functions for each type of puzzle, not caring where the messages
come from, Bluetooth or not.
